content.question: Which of the following is one of Sigmund Freud’s most significant contributions to twentieth-century thought?

choices.label: Unconscious psychological energy is sexual energy.
Dreams are unrelated to waking thought.
Family life has little to do with mental illness.
Each individual’s personality is predetermined by genetic characteristics.

content.answer: Unconscious psychological energy is sexual energy.

skill.text: Skill 1.A: Identify a historical concept, development, or process.
